    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Neuroethics asks: <em>what rights should people have over their own neural data and cognitive processes?</em>
        Neurogovernance asks: <em>what policies, standards, and compliance frameworks enforce those rights?</em>
        Neurosecurity asks: <em>how do we technically defend against the attacks that violate them?</em>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        These three layers are distinct but inseparable. Ethics without governance is aspiration. Governance without security is unenforceable.
        Security without ethics has no compass. Every neurorights violation maps to a concrete attack pattern,
        and every attack pattern requires both a policy response and a technical defense.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-8">
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] mb-3">Neuroethics</h3>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-3 italic">What rights do people have?</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          <li>Defines the <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">rights</strong> (Ienca & Andorno, Yuste, Farahany)</li>
          <li>Establishes <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">consent models</strong> (Beauchamp & Childress)</li>
          <li>Provides the <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">moral foundation</strong></li>
          <li>Asks who should be protected and why</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 border border-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]/30" style="background: rgba(16,185,129,0.04);">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] mb-3">Neurogovernance</h3>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-3 italic">What policies enforce those rights?</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          <li>Writes <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">policy and regulation</strong> (UNESCO, OECD, WHO, Chile)</li>
          <li>Defines <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">consent tiers</strong> and <a href="/neurogovernance/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] hover:underline">data classification</a></li>
          <li>Establishes <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">compliance frameworks</strong> (FDA, NIST, ISO)</li>
          <li>Bridges ethics to enforceable institutional rules</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]/30">
          <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-status-warning)] font-semibold">Gap: No neurotech-specific governance standard exists. Existing frameworks (HIPAA, GDPR, FDA) were not designed for neural data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 border border-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/30" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04);">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.1em] uppercase text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] mb-3">Neurosecurity</h3>
        <p class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-3 italic">How do we technically defend against attacks?</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
